-- Commerzbank close to selling Japan property loan package -source
-- 
-- Thu May 22, 2014 03:07AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, May 22 (Reuters) - Commerzbank <CBKG.DE> is close to selling a 700 million euro ($957 million) portfolio of commercial property loans in Japan, a source familiar with the transaction told Reuters on Thursday.

Germany's second biggest lender has been working to cut its commercial real estate portfolio as part of efforts to slash its balance sheet and strengthen its financial footing. Handelsblatt newspaper on Thursday also reported a deal on the Japanese property loans was close to being struck, citing financial sources.